    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-02T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="494"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/477: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-02T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 2, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. The Turkish Government has granted the extradition of Samuel Insull and the
                    Department is now contemplating having him sent to Alexandria via the Turkish
                    Mail Line vessel which leaves Istanbul on April 10 and passes through Piraeus on
                    April 12. Please obtain a definite assurance from the appropriate Greek
                    authorities that they will permit Insull’s passage through Greek territorial
                    jurisdiction in the custody of a duly appointed agent armed with a Presidential
                    warrant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
